      <descriptions>
        <description lang="und">Shallow Grammar for the National Corpus of Polish is a set of rules which was used for the automatic pre-annotation of the National Corpus of Polish at the syntactic level. It was constructed manually and encoded in the shallow parsing system Spejd (http://nlp.ipipan.waw.pl/Spejd/). It consists of 1187 rules for multiword entities, abbreviations, syntactic words, and syntactic groups.</description>
